          <p>Vintage-inspired engagement rings reference historical design eras — most commonly Art Deco (1920s-1930s), Victorian (1837-1901), and Edwardian (1901-1915). Key design elements include milgrain edging, filigree scrollwork, floral and foliate motifs, and pave or rose-cut stone accents. Lab-grown diamonds work beautifully in vintage settings — the stone material doesn't affect how a setting is designed or how it wears. I'm Suman Smith, founder of Lux Jewels. I've been designing vintage-inspired lab-grown rings in Canada since 2007 and became the first Canadian jeweller to specialize exclusively in lab-grown stones in 2015.</p>
